 :tx/rationale "INV-REFLEXIVE-007 FORMALIZATION: Fixed-Point Property of Reflexive Analysis. STATEMENT: The functions used for second-order knowledge analysis (analyzing the store's own observations) MUST be the SAME functions used for first-order domain analysis (analyzing external domain data). Specifically: find_agreement_clusters() must work identically on domain observations and meta-observations. extract_observation_links() must work identically on domain text and audit text. all_observations() must return the same ObservationSummary struct regardless of whether the observation is about the domain or about the store itself. detect_stagnation() must detect stagnation in any F(S) trajectory, not just the current project's. FALSIFICATION: This invariant is violated if any C9 function contains a conditional branch that behaves differently for meta-observations vs domain observations. The fixed-point property means: apply(f, apply(f, data)) == apply(f, data) — running the analysis on its own output produces stable results. Concretely: running find_agreement_clusters on observations ABOUT agreement clusters should produce valid (possibly empty) agreement clusters, not errors or special-cased output. VERIFICATION: V:PROP (proptest: agreement detection on its own output is idempotent). V:TYPE (no enum variant distinguishes meta vs domain observations). TRACES TO: SEED.md S6 (Y-combinator property from Session 038), ADR-FOUNDATION-006 (self-bootstrap fixed-point). STAGE: 1. CONFIDENCE: 0.9."
